Min heap is a specialized binary tree based data strcture that
satisfies the heap property:

Core Characteristics :
It is a complete binary tree (filled level by level, left to right).
The root always contains the minimum element.
Efficient for repeatedly accessing/removing the smallest value.

Example::

        2
      /   \
     5     8
    / \   /
   10 12 15

   Here:
   2 is the smallest → always at root
   Each parent ≤ children → heap property maintained

   In Java

   PriorityQueue<Integer> minHeap = new PriorityQueue<>();

